   579‚Üí## Docs
   581‚ÜíDotenv exposes four functions:
   582‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   587‚Üí### Config
   589‚Üí`config` will read your `.env` file, parse the contents, assign it to
   590‚Üí[`process.env`](https://nodejs.org/docs/latest/api/process.html#process_process_env),
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   605‚Üí#### Options
   607‚Üí##### path
   609‚ÜíDefault: `path.resolve(process.cwd(), '.env')`
   610‚Üí
   611‚ÜíSpecify a custom path if your file containing environment variables is located elsewhere.
   612‚Üí
   613‚Üí```js
   614‚Üírequire('dotenv').config({ path: '/custom/path/to/.env' })
   615‚Üí```
   616‚Üí
   617‚ÜíBy default, `config` will look for a file called .env in the current working directory.
   618‚Üí
   619‚ÜíPass in multiple files as an array, and they will be parsed in order and combined with `process.env` (or `option.processEnv`, if set). The first value set for a variable will win, unless the `options.override` flag is set, in which case the last value set will win.  If a value already exists in `process.env` and the `options.override` flag is NOT set, no changes will be made to that value. 
   620‚Üí
   621‚Üí```js  
   622‚Üírequire('dotenv').config({ path: ['.env.local', '.env'] })
   623‚Üí```
   624‚Üí
   625‚Üí##### quiet
   627‚ÜíDefault: `false`
   628‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   648‚Üí##### encoding
   650‚ÜíDefault: `utf8`
   651‚Üí
